# Bessie Enterprise FP&A Platform — Architecture & Roadmap v2.0

**Version:** 2.0
**Date:** 2026-07-01
**Supersedes:** bessie-enterprise-roadmap.md v1.0
**Status:** Architecture Blueprint — Approved for Phased Implementation
**Owner:** FP&A AI Platform Team

---

# 1. Executive Summary

Bessie evolves from a single-purpose forecasting agent into an **Enterprise FP&A Platform** supporting five capability domains — **Forecasting, Budgeting, Variance Analysis, Reporting, and Planning** — on a layered architecture designed for:

| Design Goal | How It's Achieved |
|---|---|
| **Zero hallucinated numbers** | Deterministic Compute Layer performs 100% of financial math; AI Reasoning Layer only explains pre-computed results |
| **Governance & auditability** | Every run logged with full lineage: inputs → rules applied → outputs → QA verdict → delivery |
| **Token efficiency** | Intent Router uses lightweight classification; RAG replaces prompt-stuffing; caching in Shared Services |
| **Platform portability** | Business logic isolated in Code nodes + config tables; n8n is orchestration only; every component maps 1:1 to a Power Automate equivalent |
| **Scalability** | Config-driven property/entity registry; nothing hardcoded; 7 properties or 700 — same workflows |
| **Maintainability** | Seven isolated layers with defined contracts; a change to business rules never touches orchestration |

**Interface strategy:** n8n Chat window today → **Microsoft Teams** at migration. Telegram is removed from the architecture entirely.

