## 2.1 Layer Contracts

Each layer exposes a defined contract. Layers never reach around each other.

| Layer | Input Contract | Output Contract | May Call |
|---|---|---|---|
| Interface | User message | `{userId, channel, rawInput}` | Shared Services |
| Intent Router | Sanitized input | `{intent, entities: {property, period, glCodes}, confidence}` | AI (Haiku-class) |
| Capability Workflow | Router output | Domain result object | All layers below |
| Financial Data | `{propertyCode, fileType}` | `{success, data[], periodArrays}` | Drive/YDC only |
| Business Rules Engine | `{ruleSet, context}` | `{rules[], validationResults[]}` | Config store only |
| Deterministic Compute | Data + rules | `{computedResults, lineage}` | Nothing (pure functions) |
| RAG Retrieval | `{query, filters}` | `{chunks[], sources[]}` | Qdrant only |
| AI Reasoning | Computed results + knowledge + template | `{commentary, citations[]}` | LLM API only |
| QA/Review | Full run bundle | `{verdict, confidenceScore, issues[]}` | Compute + LLM |
| Shared Services | (cross-cutting) | (per service) | — |

**Why contracts matter for migration:** each contract maps directly to a Power Automate child-flow input/output schema. Migrating a layer = rebuilding one flow against a known interface, with every other layer untouched.

