# 3. Interface Layer

## 3.1 Current: n8n Chat

- n8n Chat Hub trigger (already live)
- Session-scoped memory (10 messages)
- No Telegram anywhere in the architecture (removed)

## 3.2 Future: Microsoft Teams

Target pattern: **Teams → Power Automate trigger ("When a new message is added") or Azure Bot → HTTP call to orchestration → response as Adaptive Card.**

Migration-friendly decisions made now:
- The Interface layer only produces `{userId, channel, rawInput}` — a schema Teams can produce identically
- Response formatting is isolated in one "Format Response" component; Teams Adaptive Cards replace Markdown formatting by swapping that single component
- AuthN happens in Shared Services against a user registry, not against channel-specific identity — Teams AAD identity slots into the same check

**Design rule:** nothing downstream of the Interface layer may inspect `channel` except the final Format Response step.

