# 4. Intent Router

## 4.1 Purpose

Classify every request BEFORE any heavy processing, so that:
- Simple knowledge questions never trigger a full forecast run (token + latency savings)
- Each domain gets a specialized workflow with a minimal, focused prompt (token efficiency)
- Out-of-scope requests are rejected early with zero LLM reasoning cost
- Entity extraction (property, period, GL codes) happens once, in one place

## 4.2 Design

**Model choice: Haiku-class (claude-haiku-4-5 or equivalent lightweight model).**
Classification and entity extraction do not need a reasoning model. Cost comparison per 1,000 requests (approximate, illustrative):

| Approach | Est. tokens/request | Relative cost | Accuracy |
|---|---|---|---|
| Sonnet does everything (current) | ~4,000 | 100% | High but wasteful |
| Haiku router + Sonnet only when needed | ~300 router + domain-specific | ~35–50% | Equal or better (focused prompts) |

**Router system prompt (compact — ~250 tokens):**

```
You are an intent classifier for an FP&A platform. Output ONLY valid JSON.

Classify the user request into exactly one intent:
- FORECAST: generate/update a financial forecast
- BUDGET: create/modify/question a budget
- VARIANCE: explain differences between actuals/budget/forecast
- REPORT: produce a formatted report or workbook from existing results
- PLAN: scenario planning, what-if, multi-year planning
- KNOWLEDGE_QA: question about methodology, policy, process, definitions
- ADMIN: status checks, list properties, help
- OUT_OF_SCOPE: anything else

Extract entities when present:
- property: prop01..prop07 (also map: TO→prop01, TP→prop02, LP→prop03, BP→prop04, 44B→prop05, 118B→prop06, 99D→prop07)
- period: e.g. "2026-Q4"
- glCodes: array of 5-digit GL codes mentioned

Output schema:
{"intent":"...", "entities":{"property":"...","period":"...","glCodes":[]}, "confidence":0.0-1.0}

If confidence < 0.6, set intent to CLARIFY and include "clarifyQuestion".
```

**Routing logic (n8n Switch node on `intent`):**

```
[Sanitized input]
      ↓
[HTTP: Haiku classification call]
      ↓
[Code: parse + validate router JSON]
      ↓
[Switch: intent]
  ├── FORECAST      → WF-Forecast (existing Tool 6 chain)
  ├── BUDGET        → WF-Budget
  ├── VARIANCE      → WF-Variance
  ├── REPORT        → WF-Report
  ├── PLAN          → WF-Plan
  ├── KNOWLEDGE_QA  → WF-KB-Retrieve → AI answer with citations (no compute)
  ├── ADMIN         → deterministic responses (no LLM at all)
  ├── CLARIFY       → return clarifyQuestion to user
  └── OUT_OF_SCOPE  → polite refusal template (no LLM)
```

**Token optimization notes:**
- ADMIN and OUT_OF_SCOPE consume zero Sonnet tokens
- KNOWLEDGE_QA consumes retrieval + one small Sonnet call — never a compute run
- Router JSON is validated by code; malformed output → single retry → fallback to CLARIFY

## 4.3 Migration Mapping

| n8n component | Power Automate equivalent |
|---|---|
| Switch node on intent | Switch control |
| Haiku HTTP call | HTTP action → Azure OpenAI/Anthropic API (or AI Builder prompt) |
| Entity validation Code node | Office Script or PA expression |

