# 6. Business Rules Engine

## 6.1 Purpose

Centralize every forecasting/budgeting rule that is currently embedded in code or prompts into a **configuration-driven rules store**, so that:
- FP&A staff can change a materiality threshold without a developer
- Rules are versioned, auditable, and effective-dated
- The same rule set drives compute, QA validation, and AI commentary consistently
- Migration = moving config tables, not re-encoding logic

## 6.2 Storage

**Today:** Google Sheet `Bessie_Config` with one tab per rule family (readable by n8n Google Sheets node, cached by Shared Services for 15 min).
**Future:** SharePoint Lists (1:1 tab-to-list mapping) or Dataverse tables.

## 6.3 Rule Families

### RF-1: Period Rules
| Key | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| fiscalYearStartMonth | 7 | July |
| quarterMap | Q1=Jul-Sep; Q2=Oct-Dec; Q3=Jan-Mar; Q4=Apr-Jun | |
| actualsDetection | header_scan_primary, date_arithmetic_fallback | |
| trailingAvgWindow | 3 | months |
| budgetVsActualBoundary | derived_from_file | never hardcoded |

### RF-2: Scenario Adjustment Rules (per GL, per scenario)
| glCode | glName | baselinePct | upsidePct | downsidePct | basis | effectiveFrom | effectiveTo |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 41100 | Rent Revenue | 0.000 | 0.005 | -0.010 | Trailing 3-mo avg | 2025-07-01 | |
| 41110 | Vacancy | -0.100 | -0.270 | 0.270 | Trailing 3-mo avg | 2025-07-01 | |
| 41200 | Free Rent | 0.000 | -0.100 | 0.150 | Trailing 3-mo avg | 2025-07-01 | |
| 89290 | Realty Tax | 0.000 | 0.000 | 0.000 | Fixed — assessed | 2025-07-01 | |
| 89390 | Mgmt Fee | 0.000 | 0.000 | 0.000 | Self-adjusting w/ revenue | 2025-07-01 | |
| ... | | | | | | | |

**Effective dating** allows rules to change between fiscal years with full history retained — the compute layer selects rules where `effectiveFrom <= runDate < effectiveTo`.

### RF-3: Override Rules
| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| overrideMechanism | GL-keyed COUNTIFS/SUMIFS in workbook Overrides tab |
| overridePrecedence | Manual override > scenario formula |
| overrideAudit | Overrides detected at QA time are listed in run log |

### RF-4: GL Validation Rules
| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| anchorGLs | 45990 (Total Rev), 90000 (Total OpEx), 90010 (NOI) |
| requiredGLs | anchorGLs + 41100 |
| glCodeFormat | 5-digit numeric |
| unknownGLPolicy | flag_and_continue (never invent) |
| kpiSource | anchor_gl_only (never category summation — see CLAUDE.md bug #2) |

### RF-5: Materiality Thresholds
| Metric | Threshold | Action |
|---|---|---|
| Variance % (line item) | > 5% | Commentary required |
| Variance $ (line item) | > $10,000 | Commentary required |
| NOI margin plausible range | 0.30 – 0.85 | Outside → QA WARN |
| Month-over-month revenue swing | > 15% | QA WARN + commentary required |

### RF-6: Workbook Integrity Rules
| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| templateFile | Quarterly_Forecast_Template.xlsx (config: templateFolderId) |
| requiredTabs | Forecast, Overrides, Assumptions, Key Findings, _PY_Data |
| glLookupKey | Column A (never row position) |
| pyDataAlignment | Forecast-tab row number |
| staleDataPolicy | clear_unmatched_gls_to_zero |

### RF-7: Approval Workflow Rules
| Trigger | Approver | Mechanism (today) | Mechanism (future) |
|---|---|---|---|
| QA confidence < 0.75 | FP&A reviewer | n8n Chat notification + audit flag | Teams Approval / PA Approvals |
| Budget publish | Controller | Manual | PA Approvals flow |
| Rule change in RF-2/RF-5 | FP&A lead | Google Sheet edit history | SharePoint list versioning + approval |

## 6.4 Rules Engine Access Pattern

```
[Capability workflow starts]
      ↓
[Shared Services: getRules(ruleFamilies[], context{property, runDate})]
      ↓  (cache hit? return cached — 15 min TTL)
[Google Sheets read → filter by effective dates + property scope]
      ↓
[Return rules[] to compute layer AND to QA layer]  ← same rules, both places
```

**Critical consistency property:** compute and QA read the SAME resolved rule set from the SAME run context. QA never re-derives rules independently — this prevents "compute used the new threshold, QA validated against the old one" drift.

