# 7. Deterministic Compute Layer

## 7.1 Principle (Non-Negotiable)

> **AI explains. Code calculates.** No LLM ever produces, transforms, or adjusts a financial figure. Every number a user sees was computed by versioned JavaScript executing in a Code node (or, post-migration, an Office Script), from source data, under config-driven rules, with recorded lineage.

## 7.2 Compute Modules (current + planned)

| Module | Status | Function |
|---|---|---|
| `compute-financials-v4.js` | ✅ Live | 3-scenario forecast, KPI derivation from anchor GLs, period auto-derivation from file headers |
| `generate-excel-workbook-dynamic.js` | ✅ Live | Template population (any quarter), formula generation per forecast column, stale-data clearing |
| `variance-calc.js` | 🔜 Phase 2 | Budget-vs-actual and forecast-vs-budget variance with materiality tagging from RF-5 |
| `budget-build.js` | 🔜 Phase 3 | Driver-based budget construction from prior actuals + RF-2 rules |
| `consolidate.js` | 🔜 Phase 4 | Multi-property portfolio rollup |

## 7.3 Lineage Object

Every compute run emits a lineage record alongside results:

```json
{
  "runId": "uuid",
  "module": "compute-financials-v4",
  "moduleVersion": "4.1",
  "inputs": {
    "actualsFile": {"name": "prop01_actuals.xlsx", "driveId": "...", "modifiedTime": "..."},
    "rulesApplied": ["RF-1@v3", "RF-2@v5", "RF-4@v2"]
  },
  "derived": {"period": "2026-Q4", "fiscalYear": "FY2026", "actualsMonths": 9},
  "outputs": {"keyFindingsHash": "sha256:..."}
}
```

Lineage is written to the audit log and is what makes every number in every workbook traceable to its exact inputs and rule versions.

## 7.4 Migration Mapping

| n8n Code node | Power Automate equivalent |
|---|---|
| compute-financials | Office Script (TypeScript port — logic is plain JS, ports directly) or Azure Function |
| generate-workbook | **Office Script on live Excel file** — this is an upgrade: conditional formatting + dropdowns preserved (SheetJS limitation disappears) |
| variance/budget/consolidate | Office Scripts or Azure Functions |

Because compute modules are pure functions (data + rules in → results out, no n8n API usage inside the math), they port with minimal rework. This was a deliberate constraint.
# 8. RAG Knowledge Layer

## 8.1 Scope Boundary (Critical)

RAG stores **business knowledge**, never financial data:

| Content | RAG? | Lives in |
|---|---|---|
| Forecasting/budgeting SOPs & methodology | ✅ | Knowledge Base |
| Per-GL forecasting guidance | ✅ | Knowledge Base |
| Accounting policies, KPI definitions, glossary | ✅ | Knowledge Base |
| Historical variance commentary (approved) | ✅ | Knowledge Base |
| Approval processes, materiality frameworks | ✅ | Knowledge Base |
| Actuals, budgets, rent rolls | ❌ | Financial Data Layer |
| Computed KPIs, variances | ❌ | Deterministic Compute output |
| Scenario adjustment percentages | ❌ | Business Rules Engine (RF-2) |

**Why the last row matters:** adjustment percentages are *rules that drive calculations* — they must live in the Rules Engine where compute reads them deterministically. The Knowledge Base may contain the *explanation* of why the vacancy assumption is -10% (for AI commentary), but the number that actually drives the math comes only from RF-2. This prevents a stale document from silently changing a calculation.

## 8.2 Two Workflows

### WF-KB-Ingest — Knowledge Ingestion Pipeline

```
[Schedule Trigger — daily 02:00]  (+ manual trigger for immediate re-ingest)
        ↓
[Config: get knowledgeBaseFolderId, lastIngestTimestamp]     ← Shared Services
        ↓
[Google Drive: List files recursively]                        ← future: SharePoint "Get files"
        ↓
[Code: FILTER]
   • extensions: .md, .txt, .docx (docx → extract text first)
   • modifiedTime > lastIngestTimestamp
   • skip files without valid frontmatter
        ↓
[Loop per file]
        ↓
[Google Drive: Download]
        ↓
[Code: EXTRACT + CLEAN]
   • parse YAML frontmatter → metadata object
   • skip if status == deprecated (and DELETE existing vectors for this file)
   • strip HTML/formatting artifacts, normalize whitespace,
     remove boilerplate headers/footers
        ↓
[Code: CHUNK]  (strategy table below — by document_type)
        ↓
[HTTP: OpenAI Embeddings — text-embedding-3-small, batched 20 chunks/call]
        ↓
[Code: BUILD PAYLOAD]
   • point id = sha1(fileName + '_' + chunkIndex)   (deterministic → idempotent upserts)
   • vector + full metadata payload
        ↓
[HTTP: Qdrant]
   1. DELETE points where source_file == fileName   (purge stale chunks)
   2. UPSERT new points
        ↓
[Shared Services: audit log ingestion run]
   fileName, chunkCount, tokensEmbedded, duration, status
        ↓
[Config: update lastIngestTimestamp]
```

Failure handling: per-file try/catch — one bad document logs an error row and never blocks the rest of the batch. Retry: single automatic retry per file; persistent failure → observability alert.

### WF-KB-Retrieve — Retrieval Pipeline

```
[Input: {query, entities{property, glCodes, period}, intent}]   ← from Intent Router
        ↓
[Shared Services: CACHE CHECK]
   key = sha1(normalized query + filters); TTL 60 min
   hit → return cached chunks (zero embedding cost)
        ↓
[HTTP: OpenAI Embeddings — embed query]
        ↓
[HTTP: Qdrant Search]
   • filter: status == 'active'
   • filter: applicable_properties CONTAINS ANY [property, 'all']
   • filter (if glCodes present): applicable_gl_codes CONTAINS ANY [glCodes..., 'all']
   • filter (if period present): fiscal_year IN [FY(period), 'all']
   • limit: 8 candidates, score_threshold: 0.70
        ↓
[Code: RANK + TRIM]
   • prefer property-specific over 'all' at similar scores
   • dedupe by source_file (max 2 chunks per document)
   • cap: 5 chunks, ~750 tokens total context budget
        ↓
[Code: FORMAT CONTEXT BLOCK]
   each chunk rendered as:
   ### [<title>] — Source: <source_file> §<section>, v<version>
   <chunk text>
        ↓
[Output: {contextBlock, sources[]}]   → injected into AI Reasoning prompt
[Shared Services: cache store + log retrieval metrics (scores, chunk ids)]
```

## 8.3 Chunking Strategy

**Rule: one retrievable concept per chunk. Never chunk across section boundaries.**

| document_type | Chunk unit | Target size | Overlap |
|---|---|---|---|
| forecasting/budgeting methodology | `##` section | ~500 tokens | 50 |
| gl_guidance | one GL code block | ~300 tokens | 0 (self-contained) |
| accounting_policy | paragraph group | ~300 tokens | 75 |
| kpi_definition | one KPI | ~200 tokens | 0 |
| historical_commentary | one property-period | ~400 tokens | 0 |
| approval_workflow / materiality | `##` section | ~400 tokens | 50 |

Chunks below 50 tokens are merged into the preceding chunk; chunks above 800 are split at sentence boundaries with 50-token overlap.

## 8.4 Embedding Model

**Choice: OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (1536-dim).**

| Criterion | text-embedding-3-small | text-embedding-3-large | Voyage/other |
|---|---|---|---|
| Cost /1M tokens | $0.02 | $0.13 | varies |
| Quality for domain SOP retrieval | High (sufficient) | Marginal gain | comparable |
| n8n + PA support | Native/HTTP simple | same | extra vendor |

Full KB re-ingest (~50 docs, ~100K tokens) ≈ **$0.002**. Cost is a non-factor; small is correct. Revisit only if retrieval-quality metrics (see §12) show sustained misses.

## 8.5 Metadata Standards

Every document begins with YAML frontmatter (ingestion rejects files without it):

```yaml
---
document_type: gl_guidance        # taxonomy below
version: 2
status: active                    # active | draft | deprecated
owner: FP&A Team
last_reviewed: 2026-07-01
applicable_properties: all        # or comma list: prop01,prop03
applicable_gl_codes: 41110        # or 'all'
fiscal_year: all                  # or FY2026
tags: [vacancy, forecasting]
---
```

**Taxonomy:** `forecasting_methodology | budgeting_methodology | accounting_policy | kpi_definition | gl_guidance | materiality | commentary_template | approval_workflow | property_procedure | historical_commentary | lessons_learned | glossary`

All frontmatter fields are stored as Qdrant payload fields and are filterable at query time.

## 8.6 Versioning & Knowledge Lifecycle

```
DRAFT ──(owner review)──▶ ACTIVE ──(superseded)──▶ DEPRECATED ──(retention)──▶ ARCHIVED
```

| Lifecycle rule | Implementation |
|---|---|
| New version | New file `_v{n+1}`, old file frontmatter → `status: deprecated` |
| Deprecated handling | Ingestor deletes its vectors on next run; file retained in Drive for audit |
| Review cadence | Quarterly; `last_reviewed` older than 2 quarters → observability flag "stale knowledge" |
| Approval to activate | Owner sets `status: active`; (future: SharePoint approval flow gates the status change) |
| Deletion | Never delete files; archive folder after 2 years deprecated |

## 8.7 Migration Mapping

| Component | Today | Future |
