# 9. AI Reasoning Layer

## 9.1 Role

The ONLY layer that generates natural language. It receives a fully assembled context bundle and produces commentary, explanations, and narratives. It cannot fetch data, cannot calculate, cannot invoke tools mid-generation (all tool orchestration is upstream in the capability workflow).

## 9.2 Prompt Assembly (from Shared Services templates)

```
[Prompt Template: e.g. 'forecast-commentary-v2']     ← versioned in template store
        +
[Governance header — anti-hallucination rules]        ← shared, versioned
        +
[RAG context block]                                    ← from WF-KB-Retrieve
        +
[Computed results — keyFindings JSON]                  ← from Deterministic Compute
        +
[Task instruction + output schema]
        ↓
[HTTP: Claude Sonnet call — temp 0.2, max_tokens per template config]
        ↓
[Code: validate output against expected schema; strip anything non-conforming]
```

## 9.3 Model Tiering

| Task | Model | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Intent classification, entity extraction | Haiku-class | Classification needs no reasoning depth |
| Commentary, variance narrative, KB answers | Sonnet-class | Language quality + instruction-following |
| QA Tier-2 structured review | Haiku-class first; Sonnet only if Haiku returns UNCERTAIN | Narrow yes/no questions; escalate only ambiguity |

## 9.4 Anti-Hallucination Governance Header (v7 — include verbatim in every reasoning prompt)

```
## NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES
1. NEVER produce a number that is not present verbatim in the COMPUTED RESULTS
   or RETRIEVED KNOWLEDGE sections. If a figure is unavailable, write
   "not available in this run".
2. NEVER perform arithmetic — no sums, differences, ratios, or percentages
   you compute yourself.
3. NEVER reference a property, GL code, or account name absent from the inputs.
4. EVERY factual claim carries a source tag:
   [Compute: keyFindings.<field>] | [Yardi GL <code>] |
   [KB: <source_file> §<section>] | [Rule: RF-<n>]
5. Disclose any dataQuality.warningFlags BEFORE presenting results.
6. When uncertain, say so. "I cannot confirm this from available data"
   is always acceptable.
```

## 9.5 Token Budget (per forecast run, Sonnet call)

| Component | Tokens |
|---|---|
| Template + governance header | ~500 |
| RAG context (≤5 chunks) | ~750 |
| keyFindings JSON | ~800 |
| Conversation memory (trimmed to 6 messages) | ~700 |
| **Input total** | **~2,750** |
| Output budget | ~1,000 |

Enforced by Shared Services: the prompt assembler hard-trims RAG context first, then memory, if the input exceeds 3,000 tokens. Overflow events are logged as observability metrics.

