# 10. QA / Review Layer (Tool 7)

## 10.1 Architecture: Deterministic-First

~80% of validation is pure code; the LLM sees only narrow, structured questions. The QA layer reads the SAME resolved rule set (from the run context) that compute used.

## 10.2 Validation Categories

### Tier 1 — Deterministic (Code node; binary PASS/WARN/FAIL)

| Category | Checks |
|---|---|
| **Calculation validation** | ytd_total == Σ monthly actuals (0.1% tolerance) per anchor GL; NOI == Revenue − OpEx; forecast_total == Σ forecast months per scenario; workbook keyFindings hash matches compute lineage hash |
| **Period integrity** | forecastMonths strictly after actualsMonths; actuals+forecast == 12 (or flagged); derived period label consistent with forecastMonths[0]; trailing window == RF-1.trailingAvgWindow |
| **Business rule compliance** | Scenario ordering (Downside ≤ Baseline ≤ Upside for NOI); adj percentages used == RF-2 effective values; anchor-GL KPI sourcing (RF-4); materiality-flagged lines (RF-5) each have commentary present |
| **Workbook integrity** | All RF-6 required tabs present; GL column-A lookup intact; _PY_Data row alignment; no stale non-zero GLs outside current actuals set |
| **Schema/data quality** | keyFindings fields present + typed; NOI margin within RF-5 plausible range; required anchor GLs present in actuals |

### Tier 2 — LLM Structured Review (only if Tier 1 has no FAIL)

Six fixed questions, answers restricted to PASS/FAIL/UNCERTAIN + one sentence:

1. Commentary YTD Revenue matches keyFindings.ytdRevenue?
2. Commentary NOI margin matches keyFindings.ytdNOIMargin?
3. Top favourable/unfavourable variances cited match keyFindings arrays?
4. **Every numeric claim in commentary is supported by keyFindings?**
5. **Every [KB: ...] citation corresponds to a chunk actually retrieved this run?** ← retrieved-knowledge validation
6. Commentary contains no estimates/calculations of its own?

Question 5 closes the loop on RAG: the QA layer receives the retrieval log (chunk ids + sources) and verifies the AI cited only knowledge it was actually given — the direct hallucination indicator for the knowledge layer.

### Source Attribution Check (deterministic, regex-based)

Every sentence containing a number must contain a source tag (`[Compute:`, `[Yardi GL`, `[KB:`, `[Rule:`). Untagged numeric sentences → FAIL with the sentence quoted.

## 10.3 Confidence Score

```
score = (Σ PASS + 0.5 × Σ WARN) / total checks
weights: Tier-1 calculation & rule checks ×2 (failures here are worst)
```

| Score | Verdict | Action |
|---|---|---|
| ≥ 0.90 | PASS | Deliver with "✅ QA-verified" badge |
| 0.75–0.89 | PASS-WITH-NOTES | Deliver + disclosure of WARNs |
| 0.60–0.74 | RETRY | Auto-retry (max 2) with correction hints |
| < 0.60 or any Tier-1 FAIL in calculation category | ESCALATE | Human review; do not deliver |

## 10.4 Retry & Escalation Flow

```
[QA verdict]
   ├── PASS / PASS-WITH-NOTES → deliver (badge + citations + confidence)
   ├── RETRY (attempt ≤ 2)
   │      ↓
   │   classify failure:
   │     • commentary-only issue → re-run AI Reasoning ONLY with hint:
   │       "Previous draft failed QA: <issues>. Correct these; numbers unchanged."
   │       (cheap — no recompute)
   │     • compute/data issue → re-run capability workflow with hint in run context
   │      ↓
   │   [QA re-runs on new output] → back to verdict
   └── ESCALATE
          ↓
       audit log: qa_result=ESCALATED, issues[]
       notify user: "This output requires human review before delivery — <summary>"
       notify reviewer channel (n8n Chat today; Teams @mention + Approval at migration)
       hold artifact in yardi-output/_pending_review/
```

Retry budget is enforced by run context (`retryCount`), hard-capped at 2 — runaway-cost protection.

## 10.5 QA Outputs (persisted per run)

```json
{
  "runId": "...", "verdict": "PASS", "confidenceScore": 0.94,
  "tier1": [{"check":"ytd_reconciliation_45990","result":"PASS"}, ...],
  "tier2": [{"q":5,"result":"PASS"}, ...],
  "attributionCoverage": 1.0,
  "retryCount": 0,
  "issues": []
}
```
# 11. Shared Services

Cross-cutting services every workflow consumes. Each is small, isolated, and maps to a Power Automate/Azure equivalent.

## 11.1 Authentication & Authorization

| Aspect | Today (n8n Chat) | Future (Teams) |
|---|---|---|
| Identity | n8n session user id | AAD identity (from Teams context) |
| User registry | Google Sheet `Bessie_Config` → `Users` tab: userId, displayName, role, active | AAD security groups / SharePoint list |
| Roles | `viewer` (KNOWLEDGE_QA + REPORT only), `analyst` (all capabilities), `admin` (+ config changes) | same roles, group-mapped |
| Enforcement point | First Code node after trigger: lookup userId → role → allowed intents; unauthorized intent → refusal template (zero LLM cost) | PA condition on group membership |

Principle of least privilege: role gates are per-intent, not all-or-nothing.

## 11.2 Secrets Management

| Secret | Location | Rotation |
|---|---|---|
| Anthropic / OpenAI / SerpAPI keys | n8n credential store (encrypted at rest — ensure `N8N_ENCRYPTION_KEY` is set) | Quarterly; calendar-driven |
| Qdrant API key | Docker env var `QDRANT_API_KEY` | Quarterly |
| Google OAuth | n8n credential store | Reconnect on expiry symptom (all-branches-not-found) |
| Rules/config sheet IDs | Config Registry (not secret, but centralized) | — |

Rules: no keys in Code nodes ever (`process.env.*` only); no keys in GitHub; future: Azure Key Vault at migration, referenced from PA connections.

## 11.3 Configuration Registry

Single Google Sheet `Bessie_Config` (tabs: `Properties`, `Users`, `RuleFamilies` [RF-1..RF-7 tabs], `System`), cached 15 min in workflow static data. `System` tab holds folder IDs, template filename, model names, token budgets, QA thresholds, retry caps, KB folder id, Qdrant collection name.

**Everything that could plausibly change lives here. Zero hardcoded values in workflows.** Migration: 1:1 to SharePoint Lists.

## 11.4 Prompt Template Store

Templates versioned in GitHub `/prompts/` (source of truth) and mirrored into the Config sheet for runtime retrieval:

| Template | Used by |
|---|---|
| `intent-router-v1` | Intent Router |
| `governance-header-v7` | prepended to ALL reasoning prompts |
| `forecast-commentary-v2` | WF-Forecast |
| `variance-narrative-v1` | WF-Variance |
| `kb-answer-v1` | KNOWLEDGE_QA path |
| `qa-tier2-review-v1` | QA Layer |

Changing a template = GitHub PR + sheet update; runs log which template version they used (lineage).

## 11.5 Audit Logging

Google Sheet `Bessie_Audit_Log` (append-only; annual archive), one row per run:

`run_id, timestamp, user_id, role, channel, intent, property, period, fiscal_year, rules_versions, template_versions, files_found, kb_chunks_used, qa_verdict, confidence, retry_count, qa_issues, output_file, tokens_router, tokens_reasoning, tokens_qa, duration_s, error`

Plus secondary logs: `KB_Ingest_Log`, `Retrieval_Log` (chunk ids + scores per query — feeds observability). Migration: SharePoint List or Dataverse.

## 11.6 Caching

| Cache | Key | TTL | Benefit |
|---|---|---|---|
| Config/rules | sheet tab | 15 min | avoids re-reading config every run |
| KB retrieval | sha1(query+filters) | 60 min | repeated questions cost zero embeddings |
| Template store | template id | 15 min | — |

Implementation: n8n workflow static data today; Redis only if volume demands (not yet). PA equivalent: cached SharePoint reads / Dataverse.

