# 14. Migration Strategy — SharePoint, Teams, Power Automate

## 14.1 Component Mapping

| Layer / Service | n8n implementation | Target implementation |
|---|---|---|
| Interface | n8n Chat | Teams + Azure Bot / PA Teams trigger; Adaptive Cards |
| Intent Router | Haiku HTTP + Switch | PA Switch + HTTP (Azure OpenAI/Anthropic) or AI Builder |
| Capability workflows | Sub-workflows | PA child flows (contracts already defined) |
| Financial Data | Drive nodes | SharePoint connector or YDC HTTP (preferred) |
| Rules Engine | Google Sheet tabs | SharePoint Lists / Dataverse (1:1) |
| Compute | JS Code nodes | **Office Scripts** (JS→TS port) or Azure Functions |
| Workbook generation | SheetJS | **Office Script on live Excel — CF + dropdowns preserved (limitation removed)** |
| RAG ingestion | n8n scheduled flow | PA scheduled flow + SharePoint file triggers |
| Vector DB | Qdrant Cloud | Unchanged (HTTPS API) or Azure AI Search |
| Embeddings | OpenAI | Azure OpenAI (same model family — no re-embedding) |
| Prompt store | GitHub + sheet | GitHub + SharePoint list |
| Audit/metrics | Google Sheets | SharePoint Lists / Dataverse + Power BI |
| Approvals | Notification + hold folder | PA Approvals (native) |
| Secrets | n8n credentials + env | Azure Key Vault + PA connections |

## 14.2 Migration Order (lowest risk first)

1. **Workbook generation → Office Script** (immediate quality gain: formatting preserved; smallest blast radius)
2. **Document/knowledge store → SharePoint** (enables SharePoint-native ingestion triggers)
3. **Config/rules/audit → SharePoint Lists** (unlocks PA Approvals on rule changes)
4. **Interface → Teams** (user-facing switch; everything behind contracts is unchanged)
5. **Orchestration → PA child flows** (last — by now every dependency is already Microsoft-side)
6. **Data → YDC API** (independent track; can happen any time after Phase 5 spike)

## 14.3 Migration Gates (per component)

- Contract parity test: same inputs → byte-equivalent outputs (compute) or schema-equivalent (others)
- Dual-run window: n8n and PA versions run in parallel on identical inputs for ≥ 5 runs; diffs reviewed
- Audit continuity: run_ids and lineage uninterrupted across the cutover
- Rollback: previous n8n workflow retained, disabled-not-deleted, for 60 days

## 14.4 Design Decisions Already Made for Migration Ease

- Compute modules are pure functions — no n8n API usage inside math → direct TS port
- Layer contracts are JSON schemas — PA child-flow I/O maps 1:1
- Nothing reads `channel` except final formatting → Teams swap is one component
- Config-driven everything → migration moves tables, not logic
- Qdrant + OpenAI chosen for platform-agnostic HTTPS APIs → survive the migration unchanged

